---
const fastFacts = [
  { label: 'Population', value: 'Approx. 1.06 million', source: 'ONS, 2021 Census' },
  { label: 'Cheshire East avg. price', value: '£306,000', source: 'ONS, Q4 2025' },
  { label: 'Cheshire West avg. price', value: '£266,000', source: 'ONS, Q4 2025' },
  { label: 'UK average house price', value: '£285,000', source: 'ONS, Q4 2025' },
  { label: 'Fastest Manchester commute', value: '17 mins (Wilmslow)', source: 'National Rail, 2025' },
  { label: 'Nearest major city', value: 'Manchester (16-30 miles)', source: 'Geographic' },
  { label: 'International airport', value: 'Manchester Airport (in county)', source: 'MAG, 2025' },
  { label: 'Outstanding schools', value: '112 Ofsted Outstanding', source: 'Ofsted, 2025' },
  { label: 'County crime rate', value: 'Below national average', source: 'Cheshire Constabulary, 2025' },
  { label: 'vs. neighbours', value: '£92k above Merseyside, £105k above Lancs', source: 'PlumPlot/ONS, 2025' },
  { label: 'Top commuter towns', value: 'Wilmslow, Alderley Edge, Knutsford, Prestbury', source: 'National Rail, 2025' },
];
---

<section
  id="is-it-worth-it"
  aria-labelledby="quick-answer-heading"
  class="section-pad"
  style="background-color: #F9F7F4;"
>
  <div class="section-inner">

    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-2 gap-12 lg:gap-20">
      <div>
        <span class="section-label">The central question</span>

        <h2
          id="quick-answer-heading"
          style="font-family: Georgia, serif; font-size: clamp(26px, 3.5vw, 34px); font-weight: 700; color: #1C1C1E; line-height: 1.2; margin-bottom: 28px; letter-spacing: -0.01em;"
        >
          Is Cheshire worth moving to?
        </h2>

        <p style="font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 17px; line-height: 1.75; color: #333333; margin-bottom: 20px;">
          Yes - for most buyers, Cheshire is a good place to live and a rational place to buy.
          The county offers strong schools, sub-20-minute commutable rail journeys to
          Manchester from key stations, and substantial countryside access at materially lower
          prices than comparable Home Counties commuter belt locations (ONS, Q4 2025).
        </p>

        <p style="font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 17px; line-height: 1.75; color: #333333; margin-bottom: 20px;">
          However, "Cheshire" is not a uniform market. The county spans a wide spectrum of
          price points and character: Alderley Edge and Prestbury average above £650,000 and
          operate more like luxury Surrey villages than typical northern commuter towns.
          Crewe and Northwich remain genuinely affordable at below £220,000 - offering real
          affordability for buyers who have been priced out of the Golden Triangle or southern
          commuter belts, though they involve longer commutes and different lifestyle trade-offs. The difference in average
          house price between the county's most and least expensive areas exceeds £500,000.
        </p>

        <p style="font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 17px; line-height: 1.75; color: #333333; margin-bottom: 32px;">
          Cheshire may not suit buyers who prioritise city proximity on foot, require direct
          links to London (most routes involve a change), or are relocating on a budget under
          £175,000. Rural western areas around Tarporley and Nantwich also offer limited
          public transport.
        </p>

        <blockquote
          style="border-left: 3px solid #C4933F; background-color: rgba(196, 147, 63, 0.05); padding: 18px 20px; margin: 0;"
        >
          <p
            style="font-family: Georgia, serif; font-size: 18px; font-style: italic; line-height: 1.6; color: #1C1C1E; margin: 0;"
          >
            "The right question is not whether to move to Cheshire, but where in Cheshire suits
            your budget, lifestyle, and commute."
          </p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>

      <div>
        <div style="border: 1px solid #E5E0D8; background-color: #FFFFFF;">
          <div
            style="padding: 20px 28px; border-bottom: 2px solid #3D5A3E; background-color: #F9F7F4;"
          >
            <h3
              style="font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 11px; font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.1em; color: #3D5A3E; margin: 0;"
            >
              Cheshire - fast facts
            </h3>
          </div>

          <dl style="margin: 0; padding: 0 28px;">
            {fastFacts.map((fact, i) => (
              <div
                style={`padding: 13px 0; border-bottom: ${i < fastFacts.length - 1 ? '1px solid #EEEAE5' : 'none'}; display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 2px;`}
              >
                <dt
                  style="font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 11px; font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.06em; color: #999999;"
                >
                  {fact.label}
                </dt>
                <dd
                  style="font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; font-weight: 600; color: #1C1C1E; margin: 0;"
                >
                  {fact.value}
                  <span
                    style="font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 11px; font-weight: 400; color: #AAAAAA; margin-left: 8px;"
                  >
                    {fact.source}
                  </span>
                </dd>
              </div>
            ))}
          </dl>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
